<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-14-01 - Excessive End Play in Input Shaft on Spicer N and S Series Rear Axles</stitle>
    <tsi id="tSI981401" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>98-14-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>September, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>REAR AXLE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Excessive End Play in Input Shaft on Spicer N and S Series Rear Axles</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Spicer</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>2000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/01/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>06/01/1998</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>5000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/01/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>06/01/1998</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/01/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>06/01/1998</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9000
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>02/01/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>06/01/1998</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>14GDA</ucode>
                <ucode>14GDC</ucode>
                <ucode>14GDE</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 2000, 5000, 8000, and 9000 models with Spicer N Series rear axle codes 14GDA
                    and 14GDC built from June, 1997 through June, 1998, and Spicer S Series rear axle code 14GDE built
                    from February, 1997 through June, 1998.
                </para>
                <para>Input shaft leakage may be caused by excessive movement of the input shaft/end yoke assembly. The
                    in and out (end play), up and down or side to side movement measured from the end of the input shaft
                    or the flanged hex nut is considered excessive when greater than 0.025 inch.
                    <emph type="bold">DO NOT</emph>
                    take measurements from the ears of the yoke.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <title>NOTICE</title>
                </para>
                <para>The information supplied herein has been furnished by the manufacturer for use with its product.
                    Navistar International Transportation Corp. reprints this information based on representations made
                    to the Company by the manufacturer and is not responsible for any errors or mishaps resulting from
                    such errors or from any misuse of the product. Every user is urged to carefully follow the
                    instructions which accompany the product.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
